<ProjectDetailsPage projectId="swiftborders" locale="en">
  <h2>About SwiftBorders</h2>
  <p>
    SwiftBorders brings colored window borders to macOS 15+, highlighting the
    currently active window. It serves as a perfect companion for window
    managers like AeroSpace and yabai. Built entirely on public Accessibility
    and AppKit APIs, it is designed to be stable and keep working across future
    macOS releases without requiring system integrity protection (SIP)
    disabling.
  </p>
  <p>
    For more details on how to configure border colors, widths, and integrate it
    with your workflow, please read the <a
      href="https://github.com/albibenni/SwiftBorders#readme"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener">official README on GitHub</a
    >.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>

  <h3>Homebrew</h3>
  <p>The easiest way to install SwiftBorders is via Homebrew:</p>
  <pre><code>brew install albibenni/tap/swiftborders</code></pre>
</ProjectDetailsPage>
